						<summary>

						<p>Slab built into the ceiling of the <hi rend="italic">mukha-maṇḍapa</hi> of the Kēśava temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1690, (current) Virōdhi, Vaiśākha śu. 15,</hi> corresponding to 1769 A.D., May 10, Wednesday.</p>						

						<p>It mentions the construction of a <hi rend="italic">Kalyāṇa-maṇḍapa</hi> to god Lakshmī-Chennakēśava of Pālūru by Rāmi-Reḍḍi, son of Dēvi-Reḍḍi of Muḍiyam.</p>						

						</summary>
